<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,1415,1836]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1632,1656]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1851" box="[447,557,1632,1656]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pilumnidae" genus="Actumnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[447,557,1632,1656]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Actumnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is represented by six species in the Persian Gulf (
<bibRefCitation author="Apel, M." box="[1124,1247,1631,1655]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref45060" refString="Apel, M. (2001) Taxonomie und Zoogeographie der Brachyura, Paguridea und Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda) des Persisch-Arabischen Golfes. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Johann Wolfgang Goethe-Universitat, Frankfurt a. M., 268 pp." type="book" year="2001">Apel 2001</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Naderloo, R. &amp; Ng, P. K." pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="593 - 604" refId="ref50375" refString="Naderloo, R. &amp; Ng, P. K. L (2011) Rediscovery of the rare pilumnid crab, Actumnus simplex Rathbun, 1911 (Decapoda, Brachyura) and a new record for the Persian Gulf. Crustaceana, 84 (12 - 13), 593 - 604." type="journal article" year="2011">Naderloo &amp; Ng 2011</bibRefCitation>
), of which 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alcock" authorityYear="1898" box="[337,477,1668,1692]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pilumnidae" genus="Actumnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tesselatus">
<emphasis box="[337,477,1668,1692]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">A. tesselatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only one which has been recorded from the intertidal zone. 
<bibRefCitation author="Stephensen, K." box="[1227,1436,1668,1692]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="57 - 237" refId="ref52943" refString="Stephensen, K. (1946) The Brachyura of the Iranian Gulf. Danish Scientific Investigations in Iran, Part IV. E. Munksgaard, Copenhagen, 57 - 237." type="book chapter" year="1946">Stephensen (1946)</bibRefCitation>
erroneously mentioned St. 54 of Qais I. (Kish I.) as locality for a single specimen of the species, whereas stations 41-42 of the Danish Expedition were in Kish I., and Station 54 was in 
<collectingCountry box="[943,1022,1740,1764]" name="Iran" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Qeshm</collectingCountry>
I. A new representative of the genus has recently been discovered from the Iranian waters of the Persian Gulf, namely 
<taxonomicName authority="Rathbun, 1911" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1911" box="[1057,1431,1775,1800]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pilumnidae" genus="Actumnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis box="[1057,1259,1776,1800]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Actumnus simplex</emphasis>
Rathbun, 1911
</taxonomicName>
, which was redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Naderloo, R. &amp; Ng, P. K." box="[448,706,1812,1836]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="593 - 604" refId="ref50375" refString="Naderloo, R. &amp; Ng, P. K. L (2011) Rediscovery of the rare pilumnid crab, Actumnus simplex Rathbun, 1911 (Decapoda, Brachyura) and a new record for the Persian Gulf. Crustaceana, 84 (12 - 13), 593 - 604." type="journal article" year="2011">Naderloo &amp; Ng (2011)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
